<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="58" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,340,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named in honour of the Brazilian ornithologist Rudi Ricardo Laps, from “Universidade Regional de Blumenau”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,231,257]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from the congeneric species by the presence of two pairs of medium-sized apophyses on the chelicerae, in an unique position (
<figureCitation box="[938,1080,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1663,1687]" captionTargetBox="[264,1291,387,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,376,1669]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 18. Mesabolivar rudilapsi n. sp. 12. Chelicerae, frontal; 13. Chelicera, lateral; 14. Chelicerae, dorsal; 15. Left palp, retrolateral; 16. Left procursus, prolateral; 17. Tip of left procursus, dorsal view; 18. Left bulb, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178317/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
Figs. 
<number box="[1005,1080,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="13.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="12.0">12–14</number>
</figureCitation>
) and by the slender procursus with several ventral ridges (
<figureCitation box="[477,620,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1663,1687]" captionTargetBox="[264,1291,387,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,376,1669]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 18. Mesabolivar rudilapsi n. sp. 12. Chelicerae, frontal; 13. Chelicera, lateral; 14. Chelicerae, dorsal; 15. Left palp, retrolateral; 16. Left procursus, prolateral; 17. Tip of left procursus, dorsal view; 18. Left bulb, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178317/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
Figs. 
<number box="[543,620,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="15.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="15.0">15–16</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
