<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1802,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,351,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<typeStatus box="[436,553,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Holotype</typeStatus>
): Total length 
<number box="[722,762,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="2.4">2.4</number>
, carapace width 
<number box="[959,999,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="1.3">1.3</number>
; leg I: 
<number box="[1082,1133,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="37.9">37.9</number>
(
<number box="[1150,1188,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="9.3">9.3</number>
+ 
<number box="[1221,1257,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="0.4">0.4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1291,1327,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="9.9">9.9</number>
+ 
<number box="[1360,1411,1802,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="16.1">16.1</number>
+ 
<number box="[151,191,1842,1868]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="2.7">2.7</number>
), tibia II: 
<number box="[305,344,1842,1868]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="6.2">6.2</number>
, tibia III: 
<number box="[458,497,1842,1868]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="4.1">4.1</number>
, tibia IV: 
<number box="[611,651,1842,1868]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="6.4">6.4</number>
, tibia I L/d: 
<number box="[793,826,1842,1868]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="71.0">71</number>
. Carapace light brown; sternum light ochre. Distinct thoracic groove. Eight eyes on slightly elevated ocular area; distance PME–ALE about 
<number box="[1169,1200,1882,1908]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="60.0">60</number>
% of PME diameter. Chelicera uniformly light brown, basal segment of chelicera with one ventro-prolateral median apophysis, and one more proximal prolateral protrusion (
<figureCitation box="[640,785,1962,1988]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1663,1687]" captionTargetBox="[264,1291,387,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,376,1669]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 18. Mesabolivar rudilapsi n. sp. 12. Chelicerae, frontal; 13. Chelicera, lateral; 14. Chelicerae, dorsal; 15. Left palp, retrolateral; 16. Left procursus, prolateral; 17. Tip of left procursus, dorsal view; 18. Left bulb, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178317/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
Figs. 
<number box="[707,785,1962,1988]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="13.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="12.0">12–14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Palps as in figs. 
<number box="[1000,1077,1962,1988]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="16.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="15.0">15–18</number>
. Coxa with a very pointed retrolateral apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[393,482,2002,2028]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1663,1687]" captionTargetBox="[264,1291,387,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,376,1669]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 18. Mesabolivar rudilapsi n. sp. 12. Chelicerae, frontal; 13. Chelicera, lateral; 14. Chelicerae, dorsal; 15. Left palp, retrolateral; 16. Left procursus, prolateral; 17. Tip of left procursus, dorsal view; 18. Left bulb, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178317/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[450,482,2002,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Femur proximally with a small basal rounded retrolateral apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1422,2002,2028]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1663,1687]" captionTargetBox="[264,1291,387,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,376,1669]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 18. Mesabolivar rudilapsi n. sp. 12. Chelicerae, frontal; 13. Chelicera, lateral; 14. Chelicerae, dorsal; 15. Left palp, retrolateral; 16. Left procursus, prolateral; 17. Tip of left procursus, dorsal view; 18. Left bulb, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178317/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[1390,1422,2002,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,458]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
Procursus dark brown, slender and slightly curved, with several median ventral ridges (
<figureCitation box="[1179,1320,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1663,1687]" captionTargetBox="[264,1291,387,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,376,1669]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 18. Mesabolivar rudilapsi n. sp. 12. Chelicerae, frontal; 13. Chelicera, lateral; 14. Chelicerae, dorsal; 15. Left palp, retrolateral; 16. Left procursus, prolateral; 17. Tip of left procursus, dorsal view; 18. Left bulb, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178317/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
Figs. 
<number box="[1246,1320,152,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" value="15.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="15.0">15–16</number>
</figureCitation>
) and several basal prolateral hairs (
<figureCitation box="[463,551,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1663,1687]" captionTargetBox="[264,1291,387,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,376,1669]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 18. Mesabolivar rudilapsi n. sp. 12. Chelicerae, frontal; 13. Chelicera, lateral; 14. Chelicerae, dorsal; 15. Left palp, retrolateral; 16. Left procursus, prolateral; 17. Tip of left procursus, dorsal view; 18. Left bulb, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178317/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<number box="[518,551,192,218]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
). Distinct tip of procursus, ending in a membrane, with a ventral projection (
<figureCitation box="[159,247,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1663,1687]" captionTargetBox="[264,1291,387,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,376,1669]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 18. Mesabolivar rudilapsi n. sp. 12. Chelicerae, frontal; 13. Chelicera, lateral; 14. Chelicerae, dorsal; 15. Left palp, retrolateral; 16. Left procursus, prolateral; 17. Tip of left procursus, dorsal view; 18. Left bulb, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178317/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<number box="[215,247,232,258]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
). Bulb simple, with no transparent projection, embolar division of bulb membranous at the end (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1663,1687]" captionTargetBox="[264,1291,387,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,376,1669]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 18. Mesabolivar rudilapsi n. sp. 12. Chelicerae, frontal; 13. Chelicera, lateral; 14. Chelicerae, dorsal; 15. Left palp, retrolateral; 16. Left procursus, prolateral; 17. Tip of left procursus, dorsal view; 18. Left bulb, prolateral view. Scale lines: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178317/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,183,272,298]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
). Legs light brown; without spines, vertical or curved hairs. Tarsus I with approximately 
<number box="[1265,1294,272,298]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" value="36.0">36</number>
pseudosegments. Opisthosoma globular, pale green, with some lateral bluish spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,458]" box="[199,428,351,378]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,297,351,377]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
